docs.abstract: The two companies envision a world where someone’s always bothering you while you’re writing.
docs.snippet: The two companies envision a world where someone’s always bothering you while you’re writing.
docs.lead_paragraph: IF Microsoft has its way, the vast membership of LinkedIn, the business networking site with more than 433 million members, will be instantly available to you while you use Microsoft products like Outlook or Skype. How many of LinkedIn’s members do you want to consult while also using Excel or typing away in Word? Microsoft is betting it’s a lot; this is part of its rationale for its $26.2 billion acquisition of LinkedIn, announced on Monday.

headline.main: Why LinkedIn Will Make You Hate Microsoft Word
